## Startup Rule

Default startup reads are limited to:
1. `AI_AGENT.md`
2. `docs/SESSION_BRIEF.md`
3. `docs/CONTEXT_ROUTING.md`

Do not automatically load the full doc set.
Load deeper docs only when the task type or risk level requires them.

## Lean Navigation Order

### Always Read
1. `AI_AGENT.md`
2. `docs/SESSION_BRIEF.md`
3. `docs/CONTEXT_ROUTING.md`

### Read When Needed
4. `docs/PROJECT_CANVAS.md`
5. `docs/ENGINEERING_PLAYBOOK.md`
6. `docs/TECH_STACK.md`
7. `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` (Tier B/C or entrypoint/path changes)
8. `docs/OPS_SECURITY_RELEASE.md` (deploy/security/privacy/release changes)
9. `CHANGELOG.md` (when documenting or checking recent behavior changes)
10. `AI_CONTEXT.md` (if present and only when needed)

## Mandatory Working Rules
- If confidence is below 90%, pause and ask 1-3 precise clarifying questions.
- Make the smallest correct change first; avoid unnecessary scope.
- For behavior changes, add or update targeted tests.
- Update docs in the same change when behavior, commands, paths, or structure changes.
- Regenerate AI context map only when the project uses one: `[AI_CONTEXT_COMMAND]`.
- Run the verify gate before handoff: `[VERIFY_COMMAND]`.

## Lean Context Rules
- Do not read deep governance docs unless the routing rules require them.
- Do not read the entire changelog by default.
- Do not read the full traceability table unless the task changes entrypoints, wiring, pathway behavior, or smoke coverage evidence.
- Prefer task-local code reads over broad repository exploration.

## Tier Rules
- Tier A: traceability docs may remain absent or explicitly `N/A`.
- Tier B/C: maintain `docs/MASTER_TRACEABILITY_TABLE.md` and update touched Path IDs with smoke or contract evidence.

## File Size and Modularity Rules
- Soft target: keep new files <= 400 lines.
- Hard trigger: refactor when any source file > 500 lines.
- Keep modules cohesive and dependency direction clear.

## Tier Selection
- Selected tier: [TIER_A_STATIC/TIER_B_STANDARD/TIER_C_PRODUCTION_CRITICAL]
- Rationale: [WHY_THIS_TIER]

## Definition of Done (Per Change)
- [ ] Scope completed
- [ ] Targeted tests updated or passing
- [ ] Touched Path IDs updated with smoke or contract evidence (Tier B/C)
- [ ] Verify gate passed
- [ ] Relevant docs updated
- [ ] Changelog updated
- [ ] Risks noted (or `None`)

## Required Handoff Format
- Files changed
- Commands or tests run with results
- Deeper docs loaded beyond startup set
- Open risks or follow-up refactors